text.section:
The resolution of the board authorizing the bonds:
Shall describe the projects which are to be financed or refinanced by the bond;
Shall state the maximum principal amount of the bond;
Shall describe the sources of payment of the bonds;
Shall provide that the proceeds of the bonds shall be invested in accordance with any investment policy approved by the board; and
May provide that the bonds are redeemable before maturity at a price or prices and under terms and conditions or in accordance with a method determined by the board.

The resolution of the board or the trust agreement relating to the bonds may contain provisions that:
Limit the purpose to which the proceeds of any issue of bonds may be applied and restrict the investment of revenues or bond proceeds in government obligations for which principal and interest are unconditionally guaranteed by the United States of America;
Provide for the issuance of additional bonds to finance or refinance any projects, which may not exceed the total value of the outstanding bonds allowed under subsection (b) of this section;
Assign all or any part of the board's funds or assets;
Protect and enforce the rights and remedies of the bondholders that are reasonable and proper and not in violation of the law, including covenants that shall include:
The duties of the board in relation to the project;
The duties of the board in relation to its funds;
The custody, safeguarding, and application of all moneys; and
The rights and remedies of bondholders and trustees, and may restrict the individual right of action by bondholders; and
The board deems reasonable and proper for the security of the bondholders, including covenants pertaining to the issuance of additional parity bonds upon stated conditions.

The bonds shall:
Be dated and bear interest at the fixed or variable rate or rates determined by the method provided in the resolution of the board authorizing the issuance of the bonds;
Mature at a time or times not exceeding the useful life of the projects for which the bonds are issued, but in no event shall the maturity of the bonds exceed 30 years from their date or dates of issue, as may be determined by the board;
Be issued at, above, or below par value, for cash or other valuable consideration;
Be payable at a time or times, in the denominations and form, either coupon or registered or both, and carry the registration and privileges as to conversion and for the replacement of mutilated, lost, or destroyed bonds as the resolution of the board may provide;
Bear the manual or facsimile signature of the Chief Executive Officer or one of the other members of the board. In case any officer whose manual or facsimile signature appears on any bonds or coupons ceases to be an officer before the delivery of the bonds, the signature or facsimile of the former officer is valid and sufficient for all purposes as if the officer had remained in office until delivery;
Bear the official seal of the board or a facsimile of the seal affixed to the bonds and attested by the manual or facsimile signature of the secretary of the board;
Be payable in lawful money of the United States of America at a designated place;
Be subject to the terms of purchase, payment, redemption, refunding, or refinancing that the resolution of the board provides; and
Be sold in the manner and upon the terms determined by the board including private or negotiated sale.

The bonds of any issue shall be payable from and secured solely by:
All or any part of the fees or revenues generated by an activity of the board to the extent lawfully available for such purpose;
The proceeds of the bonds and investment earnings thereon;
Any grant or gift received by the board to the extent lawfully available for such purpose;
Reserves or other funds established for the bonds under the resolution or trust agreement;
Any moneys which may lawfully be applied to the payment of the bonds, including without limitation any appropriation by the State or Baltimore City made lawfully available for such purpose; or
Any source of funds to which the board has access to the extent lawfully available for such purpose.
